    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indicator 1:  Preparation and submission of Thailand&#x2019;s BUR3
Indicator 2: Preparation and submission of Thailand&#x2019;s NC4</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2019">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">Baseline 1: BUR1 and BUR2 have been submitted in 2015 and 2017, respectively.
Baseline 2: NC1, NC2, and NC3 have been submitted in 2000, 2011 and 2018, respectively.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thailand&#x2019;s NC4 endorsed and submitted to UNFCCC by December 2022</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">All technical expert were fully on board and started preparing NC4 report.

In NC4, ONEP established taskforce comprising of designated entities responsible for identifications of gaps, constraints, and financial, technology as well as capacity building assistance at all levels (i.e., local, national, academic, and private sector) and seeking matching funds from bilateral and multi-lateral sources. 

Information on the national circumstances and other information was updated. National GHG Inventory was complied. Mitigation analysis was being conducted. Lastly, complication of adaptation works in recent years and the results from these works by ONEP and other stakeholders to provide a broad national perspective of Thailand&#x2019;s commitment to its adaptation measures was in progress.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thailand&#x2019;s BUR3 endorsed and submitted to UNFCCC by December 2020</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">All technical experts were fully on board and started preparing BUR3 report. 

Information on the national circumstances and other information was updated. National GHG Inventory was complied. Mitigation Action Analysis was being conducted where National GHG Inventory will be implemented under the advice of the national experts. Representatives from key relevant agencies working under relevant climate change sector are designated to their relevant working groups, and trained on how to prepare the national GHG inventory and how to use TGEIS, contributing to the inventory chapters for the BUR3. 

Assessment result of climate change mitigation technology roadmap preparation (including recommendations on how to cascade the operations down to users or implementation agencies) finalized by National Science Technology and Innovation Policy Office (STI) in 2017 was conducted.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
